column5: Went and gave the ice shack a go at 1-5.Had action right away and very fast bite.All walleyes were in the 12-13" ranģe good eating but fish for sure but threw them all back.Was going to stay till 5 so had lots of time.I went through most of my walleye tackle and when action was fast they would just about take anything that went down.Had a solid hr of non stop action and then i had no action.lol.Sonar was bare so tried jerking some smaller pike lures for a while but no luck.Then schools of walleye came back through and had another session of none stop action this time most walleyes were in the 15"+ range and kèpt 4 of them.Any jig color did the trip and tail hooked seemed best.Fishing slowed agaiñ and i decided to head back home to catch the earlier hockey game.Shack has not dissappointed me to much this season ans even Feb has been pretty good.It will pick up in March just before they start heading to their spawning areas.
Love hearing the bite will pick up in March,March 13 they will be on fire,gotta love a nice 13 incher for a eye sandwich,thanks for the report John,rod
Ive had some fun times there this winter Rod.Always look forward to spending a day there.
Well John you can spend as much time as you want when I'm there,you are always welcomed,March 13 14 15 16,rod
You know ill be coming to see you.
See ya soon John,be fishing 3 weeks from today
